### Environment Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/v1

### ----------------------------------------------------
### ORGANIZER ONBOARDING & SIGNUP FLOW
### ----------------------------------------------------

### Step 1: Organizer Signup Init
# Submit basic details to receive a signup OTP (default is "12345" in development).
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/organizer/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullname": "Alex Organizer",
  "email": "mohit@example.com",
  "countryCode": "+91",
  "contactNumber": "8901236668",
  "password": "Test@123",
  "confirmPassword": "Test@123",
  "acceptTerms": true
}


### Step 2: Organizer Verify OTP
# Verify OTP to register the account with "unverified" status and get a JWT token.
# Uses the single global/universal verify-otp endpoint with type = "ORGANIZER".
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "mohit@example.com",
  "otp": "12345",
  "type": "ORGANIZER"
}


### Setup Signup Token (Copy from Step 2 response token)
@signupToken = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VySWQiOiI2YTFkMWIxYmQ3ZTI2ODRjOTNjYmFkNmIiLCJyb2xlSWQiOjIsImlhdCI6MTc4MDI5MjU3MCwiZXhwIjoyNjQ0MjkyNTcwfQ.sample_signup_token


### Step 3: Fetch Categories (Optional but recommended)
# Call the category list endpoint to find a valid hex category ID for Step 4.
GET {{baseUrl}}/category/list?page=1&limit=10&type=event


### Step 4: Submit Organizer Info
# Authenticated organizer submits business name, category, short desc, and social media link.
# This moves the account status to "pending" (Under Review).
@categoryId = 647f1234567890abcdef1234
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/organizer/info
Authorization: Bearer {{signupToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "businessName": "Alex Events Ltd",
  "category": "{{categoryId}}",
  "shortDesc": "Leading provider of concert, festival, and corporate experiences.",
  "socialMediaLink": "https://instagram.com/alexevents"
}


### Step 5: Test Organizer Login (Must Fail - Status is 'pending')
# The login attempt should fail with HTTP 403 Forbidden since the account is not yet approved by the admin.
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/login/init
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alex.organizer@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "type": "ORGANIZER"
}


### Step 6: Admin Login
# Log in as the Super Admin to get an admin authentication token.
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/admin/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "superadmin@mailinator.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### Setup Admin Token (Copy from Step 6 response token)
@adminToken = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VySWQiOiI2OTZmMmEwMGE0ODU5NGFlZjg5NjRhZjMiLCJyb2xlSWQiOjEsImlhdCI6MTc4MDM4MDM2OCwiZXhwIjoyNjQ0MzgwMzY4fQ.UVpy8eXWG5kNMIfvujmVBTPIHdvuAdFXizcpfE28_hc
@organizerUserId = 6a227663a2023c86b5b23c65


### Step 7a: Admin Reviews Organizer (Approve Option)
# Admin approves the organizer. This sets `organizerVerificationStatus = "approved"` and `isVerified = true`.
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/admin/organizer/verify
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{organizerUserId}}",
  "action": "approve"
  # "reason": "Documents provided are invalid",
  # "reasonTitle": "Invalid Documents"
}


### Step 7b: Admin Reviews Organizer (Reject Option - Alternate)
# If the admin decides to reject, action is "reject" and they must supply a reason.
# This sets `organizerVerificationStatus = "rejected"` and stores the reason.
# POST {{baseUrl}}/user/admin/organizer/verify
# Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
# Content-Type: application/json
# 
# {
#   "userId": "{{organizerUserId}}",
#   "action": "reject",
#   "reason": "Business registration document or proof is missing/unclear."
# }


### Step 8: Test Organizer Login (Must Succeed after Admin Approval - Step 1: Init)
# Now that the organizer is approved, this request will successfully trigger OTP generation and return a login OTP.
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/login/init
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alex.organizer@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "type": "ORGANIZER"
}


### Step 9: Test Organizer Login (Step 2: Verify Login OTP)
# Submit the login OTP to receive the final login token.
# Uses the single global/universal verify-otp endpoint with type = "LOGIN".
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alex.organizer@example.com",
  "otp": "12345",
  "type": "LOGIN"
}


### ----------------------------------------------------
### NEW MULTIPLE VERIFICATION & OTP SYSTEM TEST ROUTINES
### ----------------------------------------------------

### A1: Send OTP to Phone (Organizer/Customer)
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/phone/send-otp
Authorization: Bearer {{signupToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "countryCode": "+91",
  "contactNumber": "9005267079"
}


### A2: Verify Phone OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/phone/verify-otp
Authorization: Bearer {{signupToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otp": "12345"
}


### A3: Send OTP to Email (Organizer/Customer)
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/email/send-otp
Authorization: Bearer {{signupToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alex.organizer4@example.com"
}


### A4: Verify Email OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/email/verify-otp
Authorization: Bearer {{signupToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otp": "12345"
}


### A5: Submit ID & Bank Verifications (Organizer)
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{signupToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nationalId": {
    "frontImage": "cloudinary_front_national_id_url",
    "backImage": "cloudinary_back_national_id_url"
  },
  "bankVerification": {
    "bankName": "State Bank of India",
    "bankHolderName": "Alex Organizer",
    "accountNumber": "999912345678",
    "otherDetails": "SBIN0001234"
  }
}


### A6: Get Verification Requests (Admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/verification/requests?status=pending&page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


### A7: Admin Audits / Approves National ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/audit
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{organizerUserId}}",
  "type": "nationalId",
  "action": "approve"
}


### A8: Admin Audits / Rejects Driving Licence (Alternate)
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/audit
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{organizerUserId}}",
  "type": "drivingLicence",
  "action": "reject",
  "reason": "Images are too blurry."
}


### A9: Admin Audits / Approves Bank Account Verification
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/audit
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{organizerUserId}}",
  "type": "bankVerification",
  "action": "approve"
}
